Thought I would add this for those that would like to be actively involved in things Astronomy, While helping out in the science.  Much like Seti@home, however alot more fun as you actually interact.  This is their main page.. however you can participate in various areas of their research. Moon, Milky Way, Solar, Helping to find new planets etc.  http://www.zooniverse.org/home  Have fun.  G

6:39 here and I just took out the recycling. Light of day is just coming up over the horizon. There's a large star to the South East of me and it's the only star visible in the sky. Can anyone tell me which one that is?
Probably Venus.  No visible stars in Tennessee this morning.
Good morning Connie. Yes it could be although I can't imagine it would be so big without arms....

Just a heads up guys,  On Dec 21st we will be able to observe a total lunar eclipse, what is cool about this is it is happening on the same day as the northern winter solstice. Something that has not happened in centuries.  http://science.nasa.gov/science-news/science-at-nasa/2010/17dec_solsticeeclipse/  Thanks for the cool links guys  G
